  "text": "Sample Preparation. Scaffold material. The photopolymer used for the fabrication of the 3D scaffolds is the organic-inorganic hybrid coded as SZ2080, and is described in ref. [CITATION_1] . Its main components are propyl] trimethoxysilane (MAPTMS), methacrylic acid (MAA) and Zirconium n-propoxide (ZPO). As photoinitiator (PI) 4,4′-bis (diethylamino) benzophenone was used.",
